FBIS4-62265 "drsov093_m_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 Tajikistan Tajik Refugees Return Home From Afghanistan Tajik Refugees Return Home From Afghanistan LD1205132794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1015 GMT 12 May 94 LD1205132794 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] A group of 480 Tajik refugees returned to their homeland from Afghanistan Thursday via a check-point in Nizhny Pyanj. INTERFAX was informed by the Tajik parliament's commission for refugees that this was the first time in the last three weeks that refugees had been sent home. The repatriates are from the Khotlon region (formerly Kurgan-Tyube) in southern Tajikistan. The refugees commission said that at least 25,000 Tajik refugees are still in Afghanistan.
